# DON'T
1: Don't put too much on one screen
http://i.imgur.com/WntrM6p.jpg?fb

2: Don't use pies and donuts thoughtlessly ... but you don't have to avoid them, either
http://cl.ly/image/3w3L1I352k3v
http://cl.ly/image/2c2p1J3b2D2a
http://cl.ly/image/0g3v3J3p0n0N

3: Don't use a map just because your data has a geographic component
http://imgs.xkcd.com/comics/heatmap.png

4: Don't assume your audience knows what you know
http://bl.ocks.org/mbostock/4063582

# DO :D

1: Give context and overviews
http://nvd3.org/livecode/index.html#codemirrorNav
2: Use color to call out important data without overwhelming
